{
  "text": "With the conditioned random conductivity\u03ba( (2) has N G \u2212 N m random dimensions and can be efficiently solved with the gPC numerical methods when N G \u2212 N m is relatively small. Given that the computational cost of gPC-based methods exponentially increases with the number of random dimensions, the conditioning significantly reduces the computational cost of gPC. Here, we assume that N G \u2212 N m is small (i.e., the number of observations is comparable to N G ), and use the conditional stochastic collocation method [CITATION_1] as a surrogate for Eq (2).",
